[30;1m340 | [0m[35m*Note*: The scheduler will only consider the current usage of the compute environment unless you spe[0m
[30;1m341 | [0m[35mFor example, a `shareDecay` of 5 minutes in the above example means that at any given point in time,[0m
[30;1m342 | [0m[35mwill be scheduled for each `'B'` job, but only for the past 5 minutes. If `'B'` jobs run longer than[0m
[30;1m343 | [0m[35mthe scheduler is allowed to put more than two `'A'` jobs for each `'B'` job, because the usage of th[0m
[30;1m344 | [0m[35m`'B'` jobs will no longer be considered after 5 minutes. `shareDecay` linearly decreases the usage o[0m

[30;1m449 | [0m[35mThere are three different ways information about the way a Job exited can be conveyed;[0m
[30;1m450 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m451 | [0m[35m* `exitCode`: the exit code returned from the process executed by the container. Will only match non[0m
